{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8cf1e1e9-75db-4652-89e1-fbc46a0c3046","content":"Here's how to skip tests with a reason in each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int x) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nAll of these will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results and display your reason message in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8a21030a-1c97-487c-b6e2-410514367b55","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":262,"requestId":"BC28:7FF88:24B089:2AD763:69FA9399"},"id":"2f101c0b-a33c-4c54-b64f-2225db82ebf4","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:04:33.102Z","parentId":"6259ad71-647d-4af4-9a13-560a2b8ccefe"}
